ishing between different sources of power in international relations, not just soft power alone.","why_cuet_level":"This question tests understanding of various elements influencing international relations beyond soft power alone.","distractor_rationale":{"A":"Soft power plays a significant role but cannot solely dictate outcomes in complex international scenarios.","B":"This assertion incorrectly elevates soft power as the singular determinant of international relations.","C":"While both assertions have merit, they do not hold equally when assessing their impact on outcomes.","D":"This option fails as it dismisses the significant role soft power plays within a broader context."}},{"q":"Statement I: India's relationship with its neighbors has been shaped by historical conflicts. Statement II: Economic cooperation has been secondary in these relationships. Statement III: Recent initiatives reflect a shift towards prioritizing economic ties over historical grievances. Assess these statements and choose correctly.","o":["I and II only","II and III only","I and III only","I, II and III"],"a":"C","question_type":"statement_based","concept_id":"political_science::india_s_external_relations","trap_option":"B","strong_distractors":["A","D"],"why_not_textbook":"Evaluating these statements demands an understanding of evolving diplomatic strategies rather than static historical perspectives.","why_cuet_level":"This question assesses comprehension of shifts in diplomatic focus over time between conflict and cooperation.","distractor_rationale":{"A":"While historical conflicts are relevant, they are increasingly being addressed through economic initiatives as well.","B":"Economic cooperation is not merely secondary; it is becoming central to India's regional strategy now more than before.","C":"Recent trends indicate a clear prioritization of economic ties, countering previous narratives focused solely on conflict.","D":"All statements cannot be true together as they present con